Retired Jamaican sprinter Usain Bolt is visiting Cape Town before he moves on to visit other cities in South Africa. Bolt is a several times Olympic gold medallist in the 100 metre, 200 metre, and 4×100 metre relay events. His visit forms part of an Athletics South Africa (ASA) development programme.
 


 


 
 
